  </sharedSelectionEntries>
  <sharedRules>
    <rule id="4a60-7f7e-c37f-a4d6" name="Independent Character" hidden="false"/>
    <rule id="97b3-810d-a09e-872b" name="Invulnerable Saving Throw" hidden="false"/>
    <rule id="2563-092a-a5bc-992f" name="Jump Packs" hidden="false">
      <description>Moves 12&quot;, charges 6&quot;
May move over impassible terrain, but not end move on it.
Counts difficult terrain as dangerous if starting or ending move in it.
Advances and Falls back 3D6&quot;
Mounted weapons may fire as if stationary even when moved.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="6bd6-e738-e144-6db9" name="Bikes" hidden="false">
      <description>Moves 12&quot;, charges 6&quot;
Counts difficult terrain as dangerous.
Advances and Falls back 3D6&quot;
Mounted weapons may fire as if stationary even when moved.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="0e80-1d1e-f91a-11fe" name="Cavalry" hidden="false">
      <description>Moves 6&quot;, charges 12&quot;
Counts difficult terrain as dangerous.
Advances and Falls back 3D6&quot;</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="4795-fd7c-2846-78ba" name="Open-Topped" hidden="false"/>
    <rule id="b4ea-750c-d9a4-e398" name="Infiltrate" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>If the mission allows for it Infiltrators may be set up anywhere on the table that is more than 18&quot; from an enemy unit, or 12&quot; if no deployed enemy unit can draw line of sight to them.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="5715-6219-5059-9bcf" name="Deep Strike" hidden="false">
      <description>If the mission allows for it units with Deep Strike may begin the game in reserve. When deployed from reserve, place one model from the unit anywhere on the battlefield and roll the Scatter dice. If you roll a HIT the model stays where it is , but if an arrow is shwon this determines the direction the model is scattered in. If a scatter occurs, roll 2D6&quot; to see how far the model scatters.
All Deep Striking models are then arranged around the first model. Models must be placed in base contact with the original model in a circle around it. When the first circle is complete, a further circle should be placed with each model touching the circle inside it. Each circle should include as many models as will fit. Models that cannot be placed due to coming within 1&quot; of an enemy, entering impassible terrain, or going off-table count are destroyed. If the first model scatters off the table, within 1&quot; of the enemy, or onto impassible terrain the entire unit is destroyed.
Units arriving via Deep Strike may not move or assault on the turn they arrive. They may shoot as normal, but count as having moved.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="b35d-993f-e267-1ec0" name="Fast" hidden="false">
      <description>Fast vehicles can move up to 24&quot; in the movement phase.
Stationary fast vehicles can either fire all their primary and defensive weapons or one ordnance weapon.
Fast vehicles moving up to 6&quot; can fire all their weapons.
Fast vehicles moving up to 12&quot; can fire one primary weapon and all defensive weapons.
Fast vehicles moving more than 12&quot; may not fire any weapons at all.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="ebe5-6318-0fba-b84c" name="Twin-Linked" hidden="false">
      <description>May re-roll all failed hit rolls once.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="e65f-0536-e057-e2d2" name="Combi-Weapons" hidden="false">
      <description>Combi-Weapons may fire either profile, but not both at the same time.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="cedc-c0a1-ffd3-1b51" name="Frag Grenades" hidden="false">
      <description>These grenades negate the effect of cover in close combat, so that models strike in Initiative order.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="9db9-94c1-ce97-f40a" name="Jetpack" hidden="false">
      <description>Moves 6&quot;, charges 6&quot;
May move 6&quot; in assault phase as normal move instead of charging.
May move over impassible terrain, but not end move on it.
Counts difficult terrain as dangerous if starting or ending move in it.
Advances and Falls back 3D6&quot;
Mounted weapons may fire as if stationary even when moved.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="b137-13a1-eb97-c5e5" name="Fearless" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>Fearless troops never have to fall back and are assumed to automatically pass any Morale test they are required to take. They can never be pinned. This special rule is agined by any independent character joining a Fearless unit, but any Fearless independent character joining a non-Fearless unit loses this special rule.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="3a88-67df-4004-176b" name="Move Through Cover" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>Rolls 3D6 and pick highest when moving through difficult terrain.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="4556-3c66-6ed4-87a0" name="Jetbikes" hidden="false">
      <description>Moves 12&quot;, charges 6&quot;
Counts water as normal terrain.
Counts impassible terrain as difficult terrain.
Counts difficult terrain as dangerous if starting or ending move in it.
Advances and Falls back 3D6&quot;
Mounted weapons may fire as if stationary even when moved.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="445e-e873-2a3f-776f" name="Monstrous Creature" hidden="false">
      <description>Monstrous Creatures may re-roll the dice to see how far they move through difficult terrain. They are not required to take a leadership test for shooting at any target other than the closest. They may fire up to two weapons a turn instead of one. In close combat they ignore all armour saves and Monstrous Creatures without special close combat weapons roll 2d6+S for armour penetration when attacking a vehicle.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="5150-e938-2792-646f" name="Vehicle" hidden="false">
      <description>Vehicles can move up to 24&quot; in the movement phase.
Stationary fast vehicles can either fire all their primary and defensive weapons or one ordnance weapon.
Vehicles moving up to 6&quot; can fire one primary weapon and all defensive weapons.
Vehicles moving more than 6&quot; may not fire any weapons at all.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="e111-c9c6-72de-1626" name="Skimmer" hidden="false">
      <description>Counts water as normal terrain.
Counts impassible terrain as difficult terrain.
Counts difficult terrain as dangerous if starting or ending move in it.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="3f9b-513f-8f10-5cc6" name="And They Shall Know No Fear" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>Space Marines automatically regroup as they fall back, even if the squad has been reduced to less than 50% casualties. If the enemy advance onto them they are therefore not destroyed and this is treated as a new assault (enemy striking +1 A in the following turn) in the same way as a sweeping advance. If the enemy do not advance onto them they are free to move, shoot, and assault normally in their following turn.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="c7ad-9a4b-bbde-8bde" name="Drop Pods" hidden="false"/>
    <rule id="d2c6-0bb0-d830-4c62" name="Storm Shield" hidden="false">
      <description>Grants a 4++ (Invulnerable) Save in melee.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="3f21-57bb-fb07-54c5" name="Flyers" hidden="false"/>
    <rule id="d831-af9c-0b53-6da3" name="Super Heavy Tank" hidden="false"/>
    <rule id="b333-4165-9b69-fc6a" name="Titan Killer" hidden="false"/>
    <rule id="7ca6-da5f-a87c-f49b" name="Super-Heavy Flyer" hidden="false"/>
    <rule id="7b1f-05c8-5a14-f539" name="Orbital Lander" hidden="false"/>
    <rule id="1449-94f0-531a-7776" name="Street Fighters" publicationId="8acd-6511-d7f4-63c7" page="163" hidden="false">
      <comment>Infantry Battle Honor</comment>
      <description>If the unit is in cover, then its saving throw for cover is increased by 1 point.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="17a4-53d8-039c-8f3d" name="Hardened Fighters" publicationId="8acd-6511-d7f4-63c7" page="163" hidden="false">
      <comment>Infantry Battle Honor; Bike/Cav Battle Honor</comment>
      <description>The unit may ignore negative modifiers for Morale checks and tests for regrouping. In effect, the unit will always use its standard Leadership for these tests.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="ea73-5c36-49dc-dbff" name="Steadfast" publicationId="8acd-6511-d7f4-63c7" page="163" hidden="false">
      <comment>Infantry Battle Honors</comment>
      <description>The unit may attempt to regroup even when below 50%</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="00c1-3769-63a9-17d7" name="Guerrillas" publicationId="8acd-6511-d7f4-63c7" page="163" hidden="false">
      <comment>Infantry Battle Honors</comment>
      <description>The unit rolls and extra D6 when moving through difficult terrain and picks the highest for its movement as usual.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="a61d-d857-0035-c7a8" name="Tank Hunters" publicationId="8acd-6511-d7f4-63c7" page="163" hidden="false">
      <comment>Infantry Battle Honors; Vehicle Battle Honor</comment>
      <description>The unit always passes any tests for tank shock and adds +1 to all armour penetration rolls.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="f6a6-34fa-127b-d52d" name="Counter-Attack" publicationId="8acd-6511-d7f4-63c7" page="163" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>If this unit is charged unengaged models must move up to 6&quot; to try to get into base-to-base contact with the enemy. You may not counter-attack if the unit was charged as part of a sweeping advance or consolidation move.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="2c8e-9381-711b-6fe3" name="Skilled Riders" page="74" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>The unit may re-roll any Dangerous Terrain tests.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="8b11-ab31-085b-a2d4" name="Rapid Deployment" publicationId="8acd-6511-d7f4-63c7" page="163" hidden="false">
      <comment>Bike/Cav Battle Honor</comment>
      <description>After both armies have been deployed  the unit may move an additional 6&quot;; treated just like normal movement. If the unit starts in Reserve, then you may add +1 to all rolls for that unit when testing to see if they arrive.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="4e72-8bb0-bb7a-be3d" name="Resolute" publicationId="8acd-6511-d7f4-63c7" page="163" hidden="false">
      <comment>Bike/Cav Battle Honors</comment>
      <description>The unit may re-roll any failed Morale checks.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="0fad-0140-d0ce-c2d4" name="Lighting Charge" publicationId="8acd-6511-d7f4-63c7" page="163" hidden="false">
      <comment>Bike/Cav Battle Honor</comment>
      <description>If the unit makes an assault into the enemy and wins, the enemy suffers an additional -1 modifier to their Leadership for the subsequent Morale check.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="300e-775c-430f-4b5d" name="Terrifying" publicationId="8acd-6511-d7f4-63c7" page="163" hidden="false">
      <comment>Vehicle Battle Honor</comment>
      <description>Tanks: Any unit testing for tank shock inflicted by this vehicle suffers an additional -1 modifier to its Leadership. 
Others: The vehile causes tank shock if it moves through the enemy, just like Tanks.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="d668-4bd9-175d-8a61" name="Fast" publicationId="8acd-6511-d7f4-63c7" page="163" hidden="false">
      <comment>Vehicle Battle Honor</comment>
      <description>The vehicle now uses the rules for Fast vehicles. However, it must still be stationary to fire Ordnance.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="493d-27e6-bb71-bb5b" name="Reinforced Armour" publicationId="8acd-6511-d7f4-63c7" page="163" hidden="false">
      <comment>Vehicle Battle Honor</comment>
      <description>Reduce any damage rolls made for the vehicle on the Glancing hit table by -1, treating results less than 1 as 1. If the vehicle is open-topped then this reinforced armour bonus will negate the normal +1 modifier for open-topped vehicles. Penetrating hits will still add +1 for open-topped vehicles.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="a371-36e3-150e-19c1" name="Hardened Crew" publicationId="8acd-6511-d7f4-63c7" page="163" hidden="false">
      <comment>Vehicle Battle Honor</comment>
      <description>The vehicle treats all Crew Stunned results as Crew Shaken results instead</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="e03c-d741-f1c8-092c" name="Skilled Gunnery" publicationId="8acd-6511-d7f4-63c7" page="163" hidden="false">
      <comment>Vehicle Battle Honor</comment>
      <description>Nominate a weapon at the start of the shooting phase. You may re-roll any missed to hit rolls with that weapon that turn. For ordnance, this allows you to re-roll the scatter dice.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="69af-f095-551d-130c" name="Minor Psychic Power" hidden="false">
      <description>See Chapter Approved 2004 page 142.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="2d1a-ee41-20f6-a6c8" name="Deathwatch" hidden="false">
      <description>Deathwatch squad members and characters are never subject to the Special rules which apply to specific Chapters (i.e. Space Wolves&apos; counter attack, Blood Angels&apos; Black Rage, Black Templars&apos; vows, etc.) and which affect their fighting abilities or battlefield behaviour. Must be equiped with bolters or combi-weapons.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="0f7e-d79a-ce04-7d3d" name="Smoke &amp; Blind Grenades" hidden="false">
      <description>One use only.

Blind/smoke grenades are used in the Shooting phase instead of the unit firing any weapons. Mark the unit as using its blind/smoke grenades by placing cotton wool around them. A unit cannot assault on the same turn it uses blind/smoke grenades. The blind/smoke screen lasts until the start of the player&apos;s next turn and until then the unit counts as in cover with a 5+ cover save. Because they count as being in cover, models in the unit will also strike first if assaulting, unless the enemy is armed with something like frag grenades, or has an ability that allows them to always strike first.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="0c1f-0e87-fbfe-a78e" name="True Grit" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>Models with True Grit treat their bolters as an aditional close combat weapon. However, a model using their bolter in this manner may not recieve the attack bonus for charging.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="b113-c6dc-bbcd-aa83" name="Slow and Purposeful" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>Always count as stationary when firing, even if they moved in the same turn. But move as if in difficult terrain at all times, and never receive +1 Attack for charging.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="2b57-da46-ec8d-9dce" name="Siege Specialists" hidden="false">
      <description>+1 on Armour Penetration rolls against enemy bunkers and tank traps. When crossing minefileds only trigger a mine on a 6.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="7a00-b7d3-5191-11c6" name="Night Vision" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>You may re-roll the dice when rolling to determine how far the unit can see in a Night Fight scenario. You must abide by the re-roll result even if it is worse.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="0d08-f104-a368-31a0" name="Hit and Run" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>At the end of a round of close combat the unit may choose to break off if they and at least some of their close combat opponents do not have to fall back. The unit falls back 3D6&quot; in any direction and automatically regroups at the end of the move. The enemy units may only consolidate.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="8539-2da3-3348-8a67" name="Furious Charge" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>When the unit charges, all models are at +1 I and +1 S</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="fea5-7a7f-584b-09a9" name="Feel no Pain" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>If the model loses a wound roll a dice. On a 4+ the wound is ignored. This ability cannot be used against weapons whose strength is at least twice the Toughtness of the model or against close combat weapons that allow no save.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="2729-1600-1d19-e896" name="Deflagrate" hidden="false">
      <description>After normal attacks by this weapon have been resolved, count the number of unsaved wounds caused on the target unit. Immediately resolve a number of additional automatic hits on the same unit using the weapon’s profile equal to the number of unsaved wounds – these can then be saved normally. Models in the targeted unit must still be in range in order for these additional hits to take effect. These additional hits do not themselves inflict more hits.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="b434-b6fb-a8b7-d8b0" name="Walker" hidden="false">
      <description>Walkers can move up to 6&quot; in the movement phase and treat difficult terrain as if they were infantry (2D6 pick highest).
Stationary walkers can either fire all their primary and defensive weapons or one ordnance weapon.
Walkers moving up to 6&quot; can fire two primary weapons and all defensive weapons.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="0869-c2b5-1933-775b" name="Rending" hidden="false">
      <description>Any close combat attacks which roll a 6 to hit automatically inflicts a wound with no Armour Save possible. Against vehicles if a 6 is rolled for armour penetration another D6 is rolled and added to the total armour penetration score.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="6f0a-684d-7a67-2dd6" name="Fleet of Foot" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>In the Shooting Phase you may declare that a unit with Fleet of Foot (or Claw, Wings etc) is going to run instead of shoot. Roll a D6. The result is the distance the unit may move in the Shooting phase. This move is unaffected by difficult terrain.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="9616-b86b-257f-f9f1" name="Telekinetic Psychic Powers" hidden="false">
      <description>1. No usable Power
2. Thunderclap: During shooting phase psyker can if successful force one enemy unit within 12&quot; and not in close combat to take a Pinning test.
3. Force Bubble: Can be used in the enemy shooting phase,  if successful the psyker gains a 2+ Armour Save for that phase.
4. Protect: Can be used in the enemy shooting phase,  if successful a friendly non-vehicle unit within 12&quot; of the psyker gains a 6+ invulnerable save.
5. Minor Holocaust: Can be used in the psykers assault phase if they are in combat.  If successful place a small blast marker over the psyker. Any models, friend or foe, including the psyker, under or touching the marker suffer a Strength 4 hit, normal armour saves apply. The psyker may not attack in close combat that phase. If unsuccessful, the psyker suffers one wound with no save possible and may not attack.
6: Flamewall:  If successful place a 1&quot; wide, 4&quot; long and 3&quot; tall piece of scenery within 12&quot;. The wall may not be placed on models or between units in assault. The wall of fire counts as cover, and any models crossing it suffer a Strength 4 hit, normal armour saves apply. The wall lasts until the end of the opponent&apos;s next turn. If unsuccesful, the psyker suffers one woud with no save possible and the wall is placed centered on the psyker. (Roll scatter for direction)
</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="cdfb-210a-9a56-ba6c" name="Movement Psychic Powers" hidden="false">
      <description>1. Supernaturally Quick: Can be used in any phase, if successful the Psyker gains +1 Initiative (to a max of 10) for the rest of that phase.
2. Tangle: Can be used in the enemy movement phase, if successful one enemy infantry unit on foot within 12&quot; counts open terrain as difficult terrain for the rest of the phase.
3. Fleetfoot: Can be used in the psykers shooting phase, if successful one friendly infantry unit on foot within 12&quot; gains fleet. If they already have fleet, they may re-roll the dice to see how far they move.
4. Leap: Can be used in the psykers movement phase, if successful the psyker counts as being equipped with a jump pack. If unsuccessful the psyker cannot move at all in that phase.
5. Read Minds: Can be used during deployment, if successful one unit may be held back and deployed after all other units have been placed on the battlefield (Including infiltrators).
6. Relentless: Can be used in hte psykers shooting phase, if successful one squad within 6&quot; range counts as stationary for using rapid fire and pistol weapons even if they moved. If unsuccessful the psyker may not shoot in that phase.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="3caf-69ca-2fbf-3c89" name="Will Psychic Powers" hidden="false">
      <description>1. No Usable Power.
2. Sense Minds: The psyker counts as being equipped with a scanner.
3. Inspire: Can be used in any phase, if successful the Psyker gains +1 Leadership (to a max of 10) for the rest of that phase.
4. Cause Fear: Can be used during the psykers assault phase, if successful one enemy squad within 12&quot; suffers a -1 Leadership (to a min of 1) for the rest of that phase.
5. Battle Fury: Can be used in either assault phase, if successful one friendly squad within 6&quot; gains +1 WS for the rest of that phase. If unsuccessful the squad suffers -1 WS for the rest of that phase.
6. Glory: Can be used during the psykers shooting phase, if successful one unit within 6&quot; becomes fearless and ignores pinning tests until the start of its next turn. If unsuccessful the unit starts falling back as if it had failed a Morale check. (But is not considered fleeing, so no regrouping is needed to continue moving normally at their next movement phase.)</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="1b98-b092-3bfe-f8ff" name="Enhancements Psychic Powers" hidden="false">
      <description>1. No Usable Power
2. Iron Fist: Can be used in either assault phase. If successful, the Psyker gains +1 Strength (to a maximum of 10) for the rest of that phase.
3. Warp Shifting: Can be used in either assault phase. If successful, the Psyker can only be hit on a roll of 4+ regardless of relative Weapon Skill or other special rules.
4. Shield: Can be used in either assault phase. If successful, the Psyker&apos;s armour save is improved by 1 to a maximum of 2+ for the rest of that phase.
5. Blessing of the Machine God: Can be used in the Psyker&apos;s shooting phase. If successful, the Psyker&apos;s ranged weapons count as being master-crafted for the rest of that phase. If unsuccessful the weapons cannot be fired. This power only works on mundane weapons, not psychic artefacts or daemon weapons etc.
6. Iron Arm: Can be used in either assault phase. If successful, the Psyker counts as being equipped with a power fist for the rest of that phase. If unsuccessful, the psyker has -1 Attack (to a min of 1) for the rest of that phase.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="d4f4-3b9f-8da8-52ed" name="Temporal Psychic Powers" hidden="false">
      <description>1. No Usable Power.
2. Slow Time: Can be cast in the psyker&apos;s assault phase after all assault moves have been made.. If successful, models in base contact with the psyker count as having Initiative 1 (Before modifiers) for the remainder of that phase. Does not affect walkers or other vehicles with an initiative value.
3. Healing: Can be cast in the enemy&apos;s shooting phase when a model within 2&quot; (including the psyker) is about to be reduced to 0 Wounds. If successful, the model is placed on the side. Roll a D6 for it at the start of the controlling player&apos;s next turn, if the dice scores higher than the model&apos;s Toughness, it regains 1 Wound. If the save is failed the model is removed as a casualty.
4. Statis Shell: Can be cast in the psyker&apos;s movement phase. If successful, one friendly unit with 6&quot; cannot move, shoot nor assault, but cannot be shot at, or assaulted until the player&apos;s next turn. This power may not be used on units engaged in an assault, and the units in a statis shell do not count towards victory conditions.
5. Warp Time: Can be cast in the psyker&apos;s movement phase. If successful, the psyker adds +2D6&quot; to his movement. If unsuccessful, the psyker may not move at all. In either case, the psyker may not shoot or use psychic powers in the Shooting phase. 
6. Temporal Distort: Can be cast when determining who goes first. If successful, the psyker&apos;s controller may re-roll the dice determining who gets the first move. if unsuccessful, the psyker&apos;s controller automatically goes second. This power can only be used in misions where dice rolls are used to determine who goes first.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="2dca-27d7-d779-65f4" name="Anti-Air" hidden="false">
      <description>Roll to hit aircraft using the firers normal BS</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="de3d-c21c-3d4f-5259" name="Immobile" hidden="false">
      <description>Once deployed, the model may not be moved unless towed.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="51f3-87b2-5634-c751" name="Smoke Launchers" hidden="false">
      <description>Once per game, after completing movement, a vehicle with smoke launchers may trigger them. The vehicle cannot fire and use its smoke launchers in the same turn. Any penetrating hits scored by the enemy in the next Shooting phase count as glancing hits.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="f055-41c4-5db5-4372" name="Searchlight" hidden="false">
      <description>During Night Fighting missions, one enemy unit spotted by the vehicle can be fired at by any other Imperial Guard units in range and with line of fire. However, the vehicle using the Searchlight will then be exposed and can be fired at by any enemy units that are in range and line of sight of it until the next turn.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="0e54-6618-9b31-0f81" name="Master-crafted Weapons" hidden="false">
      <description>The bearer may re-roll one failed to hit roll per turn.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="8af5-ea0c-2a76-26d8" name="Amphibious" hidden="false">
      <description>Treat all water features as clear terrain when moving</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="eb6e-5162-ade5-a2ed" name="Auspex" hidden="false">
      <description>If enemy infiltrators set up with 4D6&quot; of a model with a surveyor then the model is allowed to take a &apos;free&apos; shot at them. If the model is part of a unit, the whole unit may shoot. These shots are taken before the battle begins and may cause the infiltrators to fall back.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="a5a1-c9f5-36b8-b3ee" name="Bionics" hidden="false">
      <description>When a model with bionics is killed, instead place it on its side. Roll a D6 at the start of the next turn: on a roll of 6 the model stands back up with 1 wound, but on any other roll it is removed as a casualty.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="0d41-84e8-e76b-8cfb" name="Extra Armour" hidden="false">
      <description>Count the &apos;Crew Stunned&apos; result as &apos;Crew Shaken&apos; instead.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="1dda-f7ff-219c-fbd2" name="Scout" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>A unit with the scout universal special rule may make a single normal move after both side has finished deployment, but before the first round begins. If both sides have scouts, roll for which player moves first.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="248b-f3f2-c740-8df6" name="Preferred Enemy" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>Units in close combat with their preferred enemy always hit on a roll of 3+ regardless of Weapon Skill. Does not work when attempting to hit independent characters, monstrous creatures or vehicles without a Weapon Skill characteristic.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="97c2-e4b4-1e8c-5f46" name="Stealth" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>Improves cover saves by +1.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="9e00-97b1-f8fe-606a" name="Stubborn" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>Stubborn models function as Fearless, except that they still have to test for pinning as normal and independent characters joining a Stubborn unit gains the special rule and vice-versa.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="e60c-3ef8-0688-7612" name="Vulnerable to Blast/Templates" hidden="false">
      <comment>4th Edition Universal Special Rule</comment>
      <description>When hit by a blast or template weapon the hit counts as two hits on a vehicle and any unsaved wounds on a non-vehicle counts as two wounds instead of one.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="a793-31eb-f7e0-a703" name="Twin-Linked Template Weapon" hidden="false">
      <description>May re-roll all failed wound or armor penetration rolls once.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="295b-b636-f5a8-cde3" name="Master-crafted Template Weapons" hidden="false">
      <description>The bearer may re-roll one failed to wound or armour penetration roll per turn.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="681c-80d9-0aea-47da" name="Slow Rate of Fire" hidden="false">
      <description>It takes time to reload this weapon between volleys. It can fire for two turns maximum before needing a turn to reload. (ie, it can fire, fire again, then next turn it cannot fire, or it can fire, reload, fire again). The weapon may be reloaded whilst moving.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="f3b9-5a3b-14a7-34ee" name="Weapons Platform" hidden="false">
      <description>The weapons platform can only fire if at least one crewman is alive. When a battery of weapons platforms is fired at, randomize any hits between the crew and the weapons platforms by rolling a D6: 1-3 hits the crew, 4-6 hits the weapons platform. Hits against the crew are resolved as normal. Weapons platforms count as vehicles with an armour value of 10. Any penetrating or glancing hits destroy them.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
  <sharedProfiles>
    <profile id="9177-ce8a-92e3-157e" name="Flamer" hidden="false" typeId="b399-8a1b-bf0b-c5b7" typeName="Weapon">
